The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Corporate Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Corporate Briefs
                              
	 Chennai-based India Cements has posted a consolidated net profit of Rs 641.57 crore for the financial year ended March 31, 2008 against Rs 574.95 crore in the year-ago period. The total income rose to Rs 3,617.23 crore from Rs 2,624.86 crore in the previous year, the company said in a filing to the Bombay Stock Exchange. The board has declared a dividend of 20 per cent at the rate of Rs 2 on shares with face value of Rs 10, for 2007-08.                            
	 Subhash Projects and Marketing Ltd (SPML) has commenced work on the four-laning of the Jaora Nayagaon state highway by Madhya Pradesh Road Development Corporation. The project has been awarded to a consortium of SPML, SREI Infrastructure Finance Ltd, PNC Construction Company Ltd and VIVA Infrastructure Pvt Ltd                             
	 Damodar Valley Corporation and the State Bank of India have signed a memorandum of understanding to accelerate socio-economic development in the Damodar Valley region.                            
	 CARE has assigned CARE BBB rating to the long-term bank loan facilities of TDI Infrastructure Ltd (TDIL). This rating is applicable for facilities having tenure of over one year. Instruments with this rating are considered to offer moderate safety for timely servicing of debt obligations.                            
	 Emco Ltd has bagged a project from Maharashtra State Electricity Transmission Company Ltd (MSETCL) to set up a 220kv gas-insulated substation at Bhandup in Mumbai. This is the second project that Emco has bagged in the last six months from MSETCL                            
	 BIL has signed an agreement with LG Electronics, USA, to enable it to deploy LGs IRIS recognition productLG IrisAccess  as part of its Biometrics suite of solutions.                            
	 Dow Building Solutions has signed an agreement to acquire Stevens Roofing Systems and Geomembrane Systems, a business of JPS Industries. Dow plans to operate the acquired business as Dow Roofing Systems LLC.                             
	 Tata Communications has expanded its conferencing portfolio by acquiring the rights to offer GlobalMeet India, a new audio conferencing service ideal for India-based enterprises, as well as companies with strong business ties with India.                             
	 Woodland has launched its summer collection both for men and women. The womens footwear collection ranges between Rs 3,195 and Rs 4,995. Mens collection is priced between Rs 1,995 and Rs 3,495.                                                                                                                  ADVERTISEMENT                   
